This paper is focused on analyzing the relationship between usage and citations in a multidisciplinary open access mega-journal. The paper uses various statistical methods to analyze the data collected from the journal Scientific Reports. The paper does not focus on any specific computer science sub-category, but it does use statistical analysis and data mining techniques, which are commonly used in computer science research. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
